	<body>
		<outline text="August 2021" type="calendarMonth" name="august2021" >
			<outline text="August 1" type="calendarDay" name="01" >
				<outline text="I’m falling in love with Excel lol" type="tweet" created="Sun, 01 Aug 2021 15:32:18 GMT" tweetId="1421856322610421761" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1421856322610421761" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
					<outline text="Prior to last year, I used Excel in VERY basic ways. 

Like, basic tables of text lol" type="tweet" created="Sun, 01 Aug 2021 15:33:19 GMT" tweetId="1421856578660151300" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1421856578660151300" inReplyToId="1421856322610421761" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
						<outline text="I am starting to see the power." type="tweet" created="Sun, 01 Aug 2021 15:33:43 GMT" tweetId="1421856678400729090" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1421856678400729090" inReplyToId="1421856578660151300" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
							<outline text="Right now I’m using it to manage pharmacy inventory between two locations. 

CSV export, paste link to another sheet, then filtering, sorting, and custom formulas to help present the data in usable ways — and to answer questions I think of." type="tweet" created="Sun, 01 Aug 2021 15:35:33 GMT" tweetId="1421857139375620100" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1421857139375620100" inReplyToId="1421856678400729090" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
								<outline text="What’s happening, I think, is that I’m starting to *think* in data." type="tweet" created="Sun, 01 Aug 2021 15:41:12 GMT" tweetId="1421858561525788680" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1421858561525788680" inReplyToId="1421857139375620100" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
									<outline text="I pass most things through a data lens. 

What’s the desired outcome/status?
What is my decision making algorithm? 
What data do I need? 
Can I get that data directly? 
If not, can I it using other data and formulas? 
How do I want it presented?" type="tweet" created="Sun, 01 Aug 2021 15:45:33 GMT" tweetId="1421859654410424327" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1421859654410424327" inReplyToId="1421858561525788680" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
										<outline text="As I look down this path, the following feel important: 

- data access (in usable formats)
- data integrity (accuracy, precision, presence) 
- data manipulation (working it to create custom lenses/solve unique problems)" type="tweet" created="Sun, 01 Aug 2021 15:47:34 GMT" tweetId="1421860164500611076" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1421860164500611076" inReplyToId="1421859654410424327" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
											<outline text="It’s funny how transferable data/information skills are.

Tools for Thought/Excel/Web Design/Programming 

It’s all just working with data and information. Being able to play with it — create with it — think with it." type="tweet" created="Sun, 01 Aug 2021 15:49:16 GMT" tweetId="1421860590859980801" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1421860590859980801" inReplyToId="1421860164500611076" tweetUserName="brandontoner" />
											</outline>
										</outline>
									</outline>
								</outline>
							</outline>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			</outline>
		<outline text="July 2021" type="calendarMonth" name="july2021" >
			<outline text="July 22" type="calendarDay" name="22" >
				<outline text="It's my #Twitterversary! I have been on Twitter for 1 year, since 21 Jul 2020 (via @twi_age)." type="tweet" created="Thu, 22 Jul 2021 13:01:12 GMT" tweetId="1418194416255176705" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1418194416255176705" tweetUserName="brandontoner" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 20" type="calendarDay" name="20" >
				<outline text="One year. #MyTwitterAnniversary &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1417648200383614979/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 21 Jul 2021 00:50:44 GMT" tweetId="1417648200383614979" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1417648200383614979" tweetUserName="brandontoner" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 14" type="calendarDay" name="14" >
				<outline text="WELL. After some wrestling and some steep learning curves, it seems that V0.1 of the website is live and functional. 

https://t.co/coT8IWLt9P" type="tweet" created="Wed, 14 Jul 2021 16:05:26 GMT" tweetId="1415341678769156099" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1415341678769156099" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
					<outline text="• Created a Digital Ocean droplet
• Created a PagePark server*
• OPML content live-published via the Little Outliner editor*
• “Wiki” site will eventually be a GitHub Pages experiment" type="tweet" created="Wed, 14 Jul 2021 16:19:33 GMT" tweetId="1415345229415190531" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1415345229415190531" inReplyToId="1415341678769156099" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
						<outline text="Settings up PagePark on the Digital Ocean droplet meant working in command line (a first for me).

Thanks to @theshteves for helping to show me the ropes!" type="tweet" created="Wed, 14 Jul 2021 16:21:16 GMT" tweetId="1415345662577741826" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1415345662577741826" inReplyToId="1415345229415190531" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
							<outline text="Next goals are to restructure the “blog” so that it’s in more natural blog-format. 

Something like https://t.co/dVgnRPXXOZ is the bearing for that." type="tweet" created="Wed, 14 Jul 2021 16:27:53 GMT" tweetId="1415347329872408581" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1415347329872408581" inReplyToId="1415345662577741826" tweetUserName="brandontoner" />
							</outline>
						<outline text="*PagePark and Little Outliner 2 are fun and useful tools created by @davewiner. 

They are the backbone of the site." type="tweet" created="Wed, 14 Jul 2021 16:25:14 GMT" tweetId="1415346660402778112" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1415346660402778112" inReplyToId="1415345229415190531" tweetUserName="brandontoner" />
						</outline>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 11" type="calendarDay" name="11" >
				<outline text="How have I gone this long without learning the Mac command line?? 

This is fun." type="tweet" created="Mon, 12 Jul 2021 01:16:52 GMT" tweetId="1414393286505209857" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1414393286505209857" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
					<outline text="Homebrew is wild." type="tweet" created="Mon, 12 Jul 2021 01:17:04 GMT" tweetId="1414393337935798273" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1414393337935798273" inReplyToId="1414393286505209857" tweetUserName="brandontoner" />
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 10" type="calendarDay" name="10" >
				<outline text="Loving TedEd’s user experience. 

It’s especially fun to interact with since one of my courses right now is a brief intro to educational theory &amp;amp; design. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1414025982596501508/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sun, 11 Jul 2021 00:57:20 GMT" tweetId="1414025982596501508" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1414025982596501508" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
					<outline text="In particular, I LOVE that side-pane.

• Watch
• Think 
• Dig Deeper
• Discuss &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1414026235987075075/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sun, 11 Jul 2021 00:58:20 GMT" tweetId="1414026235987075075" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1414026235987075075" inReplyToId="1414025982596501508" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
						<outline text="Watch

A short animated video with a succinct and thoughtful script.
Well structured to give the learner a sense of the way the information is organized. Focus to hold attention and relay key points. 

They are fun to watch, quick, and easy to engage with. No fluff." type="tweet" created="Sun, 11 Jul 2021 01:00:13 GMT" tweetId="1414026708039184386" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1414026708039184386" inReplyToId="1414026235987075075" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
							<outline text="Think

A quick set of MCQ knowledge testing questions to reflect on the material. Testing for short-term retention helps to promote focus, and consolidation to longer term storage. 

What would be reallyyyyy nice would be integration with some sort of SRS tool, like Orbit." type="tweet" created="Sun, 11 Jul 2021 01:01:54 GMT" tweetId="1414027132444061699" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1414027132444061699" inReplyToId="1414026708039184386" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
								<outline text="Dig Deeper

A densely linked description of the contents, with plenty of rabbit holes to jump into. 

This section is AWESOME. I could spend hours navigating through these links on different videos. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1414027538008051713/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sun, 11 Jul 2021 01:03:31 GMT" tweetId="1414027538008051713" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1414027538008051713" inReplyToId="1414027132444061699" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
									<outline text="Discuss

A chance to reflect on the material and interact with others. Divided into guided and open discussions. 

Pretty cool if that’s your jam — though I’d prefer taking the convo to Twitter, since Twitter is the ultimate discussion board." type="tweet" created="Sun, 11 Jul 2021 01:05:16 GMT" tweetId="1414027981723406345" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1414027981723406345" inReplyToId="1414027538008051713" tweetUserName="brandontoner" />
									</outline>
								</outline>
							</outline>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Some of my favourite questions to research are simple ones like: 

• “What is the internet?” 
• “How does the internet work?” 
• “What is needed to create an host a website?”" type="tweet" created="Sat, 10 Jul 2021 23:54:44 GMT" tweetId="1414010227922460675" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1414010227922460675" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
					<outline text="It’s so easy to breeze over the basics of something — and take a thing for granted. 

Digging into those “right under your nose”-type questions are my favourite." type="tweet" created="Sat, 10 Jul 2021 23:55:30 GMT" tweetId="1414010422550749185" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1414010422550749185" inReplyToId="1414010227922460675" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
						<outline text="I often find that the simple answers to simple questions facilitate my best ideas. 

Fundamentals are mind-blowing." type="tweet" created="Sat, 10 Jul 2021 23:56:29 GMT" tweetId="1414010672023851009" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1414010672023851009" inReplyToId="1414010422550749185" tweetUserName="brandontoner" />
						</outline>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 9" type="calendarDay" name="09" >
				<outline text="Lol reflecting on the fact that I was excited to be done studying so that I could go study internet stuff again. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1412990305285066757&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sat, 10 Jul 2021 00:38:41 GMT" tweetId="1413658904223834114" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1413658904223834114" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
					<outline text="Self-directed learning quests &amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt; School-directed learning quests" type="tweet" created="Sat, 10 Jul 2021 00:39:08 GMT" tweetId="1413659015393984517" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1413659015393984517" inReplyToId="1413658904223834114" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
						<outline text="Funny part is that I would legit study the stuff I HAD to study, for fun — at the right time in the right mood. 

Butttt I respond way better to being able to CYOA rather than sticking strictly to a syllabus." type="tweet" created="Sat, 10 Jul 2021 00:40:43 GMT" tweetId="1413659415887196165" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1413659415887196165" inReplyToId="1413659015393984517" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
							<outline text="And yet still — I like the fact that I’m having to go through a specific series of learning outcomes via the degree program.

The structure is good. I chose the path. The outcomes connect to competencies I want to have and develop. 

But wow it’s a mental battle at times." type="tweet" created="Sat, 10 Jul 2021 00:42:25 GMT" tweetId="1413659840220700677" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1413659840220700677" inReplyToId="1413659415887196165" tweetUserName="brandontoner" />
							</outline>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="I want a medium that is sufficiently lossy, as to promote prolific creation and exploration.

But sufficiently lossless to promote building ideas like cathedrals." type="tweet" created="Sat, 10 Jul 2021 00:19:55 GMT" tweetId="1413654180313640967" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1413654180313640967" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
					<outline text="*out-of context a-ha moment while ravaging the keyboard in @knovigator *" type="tweet" created="Sat, 10 Jul 2021 00:20:54 GMT" tweetId="1413654425067995136" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1413654425067995136" inReplyToId="1413654180313640967" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
						<outline text="I’m starting to hone-in on what feels good in creative media. 

What kind of environments I want to think in and think with." type="tweet" created="Sat, 10 Jul 2021 00:21:34 GMT" tweetId="1413654593242796038" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1413654593242796038" inReplyToId="1413654425067995136" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
							<outline text="A key theme that keeps coming up is that I want effortless entry and capture. I want to think freely and chaotically. Allowing stream-of-consciousness explorations whenever that mood strikes." type="tweet" created="Sat, 10 Jul 2021 00:22:38 GMT" tweetId="1413654863569903618" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1413654863569903618" inReplyToId="1413654593242796038" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
								<outline text="I also want easy search, threading, referencing, stacking, building, remixing, extending, etc so that I can play with, iterate on, and develop ideas across time." type="tweet" created="Sat, 10 Jul 2021 00:23:29 GMT" tweetId="1413655076003004416" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1413655076003004416" inReplyToId="1413654863569903618" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
									<outline text="Full steam GO 

then

Full steam QUESTION

then 

Full steam BUILD, MIX, MODEL" type="tweet" created="Sat, 10 Jul 2021 00:24:42 GMT" tweetId="1413655385018351623" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1413655385018351623" inReplyToId="1413655076003004416" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
										<outline text="I want to remove all resistance. 

Or to consciously choose certain resistance in the form of constraints that suit a mode of thinking." type="tweet" created="Sat, 10 Jul 2021 00:25:18 GMT" tweetId="1413655535073873926" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1413655535073873926" inReplyToId="1413655385018351623" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
											<outline text="But IIII want to chose those constraints. 

Constraints shouldn’t be an app primitive. 

At least, in the widely applicable tools-for-thought genre." type="tweet" created="Sat, 10 Jul 2021 00:26:15 GMT" tweetId="1413655774014976002" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1413655774014976002" inReplyToId="1413655535073873926" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
												<outline text="Maybeeee I want constraints as an app primitive IF it exists within an ver interoperable ecosystem of apps. 

So I can use that app for a particular mode of thought. 

Interoperability is especially key if constraints are being imposed." type="tweet" created="Sat, 10 Jul 2021 00:27:34 GMT" tweetId="1413656105717223425" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1413656105717223425" inReplyToId="1413655774014976002" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
													<outline text="Wow I really took the @knovigator energy over onto Twitter here. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1413656380624474113/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sat, 10 Jul 2021 00:28:40 GMT" tweetId="1413656380624474113" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1413656380624474113" inReplyToId="1413656105717223425" tweetUserName="brandontoner" />
													</outline>
												</outline>
											</outline>
										</outline>
									</outline>
								</outline>
							</outline>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Woahhhhhh, this is a cool crowdsourced knowledge infrastructure.

GitHub with textfiles atomized to one .md per concept.

*following* &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/balajis/status/1413055681582682114&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 09 Jul 2021 15:47:55 GMT" tweetId="1413525329377902593" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1413525329377902593" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
					<outline text="Priority of learning GitHub/Git intensifies." type="tweet" created="Fri, 09 Jul 2021 16:46:07 GMT" tweetId="1413539976743108610" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1413539976743108610" inReplyToId="1413525329377902593" tweetUserName="brandontoner" />
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 8" type="calendarDay" name="08" >
				<outline text="Potent illusion. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/jagarikin/status/1413091404079714306&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 09 Jul 2021 02:48:41 GMT" tweetId="1413329230809772034" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1413329230809772034" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
					<outline text="Here’s what’s happening &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/toshchy/status/1413141299897651210&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 09 Jul 2021 02:48:59 GMT" tweetId="1413329304562372613" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1413329304562372613" inReplyToId="1413329230809772034" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
						<outline text="Production &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/timwinfree/status/1413261896506032137&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 09 Jul 2021 02:49:42 GMT" tweetId="1413329485227769864" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1413329485227769864" inReplyToId="1413329304562372613" tweetUserName="brandontoner" />
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Just got through a big couple weeks of school and work — back to learning about websites and blogs 🤓" type="tweet" created="Thu, 08 Jul 2021 04:21:55 GMT" tweetId="1412990305285066757" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1412990305285066757" tweetUserName="brandontoner" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 7" type="calendarDay" name="07" >
				<outline text="It seems like Twitter “verified” badges could be better used to signal a “verified human” rather than a public figure. 

There are a lot of bots. I’d like to have a visual indicator that I could use as a surrogate for authenticity." type="tweet" created="Wed, 07 Jul 2021 16:03:02 GMT" tweetId="1412804358182518790" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1412804358182518790" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
					<outline text="I like the existing verified thing though, so it’s probably more a “why not both” sorta dilemma." type="tweet" created="Wed, 07 Jul 2021 16:03:43 GMT" tweetId="1412804531205951493" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1412804531205951493" inReplyToId="1412804358182518790" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
						<outline text="But my hesitancy on having both would be visual noise. 

Some clever solution probably exists, though." type="tweet" created="Wed, 07 Jul 2021 16:05:04 GMT" tweetId="1412804870671900672" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1412804870671900672" inReplyToId="1412804531205951493" tweetUserName="brandontoner" />
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="A step by step guide on how to build a social scene. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/visakanv/status/1412674634848235522&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 07 Jul 2021 10:35:52 GMT" tweetId="1412722023676137477" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1412722023676137477" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
					<outline text="The beautiful thing about these sorts of threads is that every time I read one, I believe in the vision a little bit more. 

A bit more color, a bit more shape." type="tweet" created="Wed, 07 Jul 2021 11:00:48 GMT" tweetId="1412728297822343169" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1412728297822343169" inReplyToId="1412722023676137477" tweetUserName="brandontoner" />
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 6" type="calendarDay" name="06" >
				<outline text="Wonderful subtext for “I want to” statements.

Fully agree and hold the same intention for this sort of thing. 

There is a difference between wanting something and committing to doing it. 

Subtle but important. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/askyatharth/status/1412320015152336896&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 23:01:42 GMT" tweetId="1412547331992457219" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1412547331992457219" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
					<outline text="Plant seeds liberally and enthusiastically; tend to them when inspired to do so." type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 23:02:35 GMT" tweetId="1412547556140326912" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1412547556140326912" inReplyToId="1412547331992457219" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
						<outline text="These is no limit to the number of seeds you plant. 

Wanting something, then not pursuing it is not failure. 

It is freeing to dream without attachment. That’s when I’m my most creative." type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 23:04:22 GMT" tweetId="1412548001738989575" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1412548001738989575" inReplyToId="1412547556140326912" tweetUserName="brandontoner" />
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="I’m getting a lot of Twitter “Topics” on my feed all of a sudden. 

Anyone else? How do I make them go away?" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 14:46:00 GMT" tweetId="1412422585971773447" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1412422585971773447" tweetUserName="brandontoner" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 4" type="calendarDay" name="04" >
				<outline text="Paper is awesome. Tools for thought still have a long way to go to catch paper." type="tweet" created="Sun, 04 Jul 2021 17:17:40 GMT" tweetId="1411735979455565828" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1411735979455565828" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
					<outline text="Making outlines, maps, lists — drawing lines — new drafts — spreading them all out over the table." type="tweet" created="Sun, 04 Jul 2021 17:20:07 GMT" tweetId="1411736594491510787" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1411736594491510787" inReplyToId="1411735979455565828" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
						<outline text="An AR environment I’d like would simply replicate the ability to write stuff on a tablet, then spread them out into my physical surroundings." type="tweet" created="Sun, 04 Jul 2021 17:23:57 GMT" tweetId="1411737557788995587" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1411737557788995587" inReplyToId="1411736594491510787" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
							<outline text="And also better paper → electronic conversion workflows.

Lists, maps, outlines, doodles into their electronic equivalent. 

Paper as the cutting edge, electronics as the full framework and repository." type="tweet" created="Sun, 04 Jul 2021 17:26:07 GMT" tweetId="1411738105816748034" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1411738105816748034" inReplyToId="1411737557788995587" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
								<outline text="Then I’d like to choose pieces of my full repository to doodle and play with — with the full expression range and freedom of paper.

Like clicking into a node and just exploring thoughts in whatever form feels right.

Then compressing that exploration into electronic edits." type="tweet" created="Sun, 04 Jul 2021 17:33:17 GMT" tweetId="1411739909430419465" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1411739909430419465" inReplyToId="1411738105816748034" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
									<outline text="Paper isn’t always the right tool, of course. It has clear limitations. 

But wow does it ever feel freeing." type="tweet" created="Sun, 04 Jul 2021 17:35:21 GMT" tweetId="1411740429326901251" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1411740429326901251" inReplyToId="1411739909430419465" tweetUserName="brandontoner" />
									</outline>
								</outline>
							</outline>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 1" type="calendarDay" name="01" >
				<outline text="This might be my new favourite music-related question.

The answers are great for discovery and the reflective process is great for rediscovery. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/noahpinion/status/1410786720459657219&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 03:01:02 GMT" tweetId="1410795623939444736" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1410795623939444736" tweetUserName="brandontoner" />
				<outline text="This is absolutely wild. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/alexandernl/status/1410253599502962692&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 01 Jul 2021 19:06:47 GMT" tweetId="1410676275673538562" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1410676275673538562" tweetUserName="brandontoner" />
				</outline>
			</outline>
		<outline text="June 2021" type="calendarMonth" name="june2021" >
			<outline text="June 25" type="calendarDay" name="25" >
				<outline text="Language compresses the true experience of reality. https://t.co/ggyYK8RFvm" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 11:40:49 GMT" tweetId="1408389715187884032" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1408389715187884032" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
					<outline text="Precise speech helps to minimize the lossiness of communication." type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 11:44:39 GMT" tweetId="1408390679403896835" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1408390679403896835" inReplyToId="1408389715187884032" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
						<outline text="You’re still pointing at something — but you’re at least using a better pointer." type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 12:09:24 GMT" tweetId="1408396910096945157" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1408396910096945157" inReplyToId="1408390679403896835" tweetUserName="brandontoner" />
						</outline>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="June 24" type="calendarDay" name="24" >
				<outline text="I’m tired of training Google visual recognition algorithms with reCAPTCHA." type="tweet" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2021 21:11:53 GMT" tweetId="1408171041436938243" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1408171041436938243" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
					<outline text="Is there not another way to prove my human-ness?" type="tweet" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2021 21:12:42 GMT" tweetId="1408171245187776513" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1408171245187776513" inReplyToId="1408171041436938243" tweetUserName="brandontoner" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="I enjoy meme formats as much as I enjoy memes." type="tweet" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2021 16:31:30 GMT" tweetId="1408100479423455240" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1408100479423455240" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
					<outline text="Meta-memes" type="tweet" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2021 16:32:04 GMT" tweetId="1408100622516338692" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1408100622516338692" inReplyToId="1408100479423455240" tweetUserName="brandontoner" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="Deleted tweets should flatten as an image when quote-tweeted by others." type="tweet" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2021 16:26:03 GMT" tweetId="1408099109819518977" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1408099109819518977" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
					<outline text="As in, if a tweet is deleted once its quote-tweeted — it should exist in the quoted context as a flattened copy." type="tweet" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2021 16:26:46 GMT" tweetId="1408099288819900426" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1408099288819900426" inReplyToId="1408099109819518977" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
						<outline text="Otherwise it sets up some brutal house-of-cards shit." type="tweet" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2021 16:27:12 GMT" tweetId="1408099400413585413" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1408099400413585413" inReplyToId="1408099288819900426" tweetUserName="brandontoner" />
						</outline>
					</outline>
				</outline>
